# DNS Health Checker Script

A simple script to check DNS resolution for multiple domains. Useful for quickly verifying if domains are resolving correctly.

## Features

- Checks if domains resolve successfully.
- Works on both **Linux/Ubuntu** and **Windows Git Bash**.
- Uses `nslookup` (cross-platform compatible).

## Prerequisites

**Linux / Ubuntu:**
- `nslookup` (usually included in `dnsutils`)  
  Install if missing:

  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install dnsutils -y

##Windows (Git Bash / PowerShell):##

nslookup is included by default.

Usage

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/dns-health-checker.git
cd dns-health-checker


Make the script executable (Linux/Ubuntu):

chmod +x dns_check.sh


Run the script:

./dns_check.sh


Example Output
Checking google.com ...
DNS Resolution Success
----------------------
Checking github.com ...
DNS Resolution Success
----------------------
Checking example.com ...
DNS Resolution Failed
----------------------
